{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"10fd6c53-87c5-4946-a5f2-33fbc5f8d98e","content":"For a web API with authentication, here are your main options:\n\n**Templates:**\n- `dotnet new webapi` — ASP.NET Core Web API (most common)\n- `dotnet new webapiaot` — Web API with Native AOT (minimal, high-perf)\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth` flag):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD (org accounts) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n\n**Example:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --name MyApi\n```\n\nFor token-based auth without Azure AD, use `--auth None` and add JWT Bearer manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer`.\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a project with a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"57ea5223-c8d9-4b93-88a0-0148672a6a63","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET/web development question. Let me check if there's relevant content in the current working directory or if this is just a general knowledge question.\n\nLet me look at the current directory to see if there's any context.","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"601B:16BC0E:500BBDF:582EC6E:69F9F961"},"id":"1db77ab3-7525-451e-b191-b6e5a283843a","timestamp":"2026-05-05T14:06:39.334Z","parentId":"0e731593-0922-4caf-8ae1-b61a1ff6b6ee"}
